topics.title: Capacitive Reactance
topics.description: The phenomenon where current consistently leads voltage in alternating current circuits. This is due to the force changing, causing water flow to lead the force.
evidence_quotes: This behavior closely mirrors how a capacitor operates in an electrical circuit.
But in alternating current, current consistently leads voltage.

topics.title: Capacitor Operation
topics.description: A capacitor does not allow current to pass through in direct current, but it allows current to consistently lead voltage in alternating current.
evidence_quotes: In direct current, where the voltage is constant, the capacitor does not allow current to pass through.
But in alternating current, current consistently leads voltage.

topics.title: Impedance
topics.description: The cumulative effect of resistance, inductive reactance, and capacitive reactance on the current within a circuit.
evidence_quotes: The cumulative effect of these factors is referred to as impedance.
